### TEST INSTRUCTIONS


## How run test

run "truffle test"


# Test instructions

There are 3 js file of test:


# TestERC721Mintable.js

It's used to test contract ERC721Mintable contract!

- Test initialize contract and mint 3 token
  
- 1 - should return total supply : check method total supply is working correctly

- 2 - should get token balance : check method balanceOf is working correctly 

- 3 - should return token uri: check tokenURI is saved correctly as BaseTokenUri + tokenId

- 4 - should transfer token from one owner to another: use function transferFrom to transfer token from an address to another

- 5 - should fail to mint when address is not contract owner': try to mint a token when you're not the owner! It will throw the exception!

- 6 - should return contract owner : try to mint a new token and let's if the owner is correctly registered by function ownerOf(tokenId)


# TestSquareVerifier.js

It's used to test contract SquareVerifier contract! Remember that SquareVerifier is been producted by zokrates following the guide https://classroom.udacity.com/nanodegrees/nd1309/parts/36b45ada-c0e5-495e-b6cc-34ea14a18d61/modules/996c54f8-4fa5-4eee-98c3-25788c8a5fc5/lessons/d35b025b-01b3-4bd9-acf5-e8bb5b88f00c/concepts/a431480a-c27c-437d-a911-8d442d2c8624
(I renamed verifier.sol to SquareVerifier.sol to try to fix a problem with inheritance)

- initialize verifier contract
  
- 1 - Test verification with correct proof: use verifyTx to verify the content of proof json generated from zokrates (verify the solidity contract generated by zokrates executed successfully)

- 2 - Test verification with incorrect proof: try to use a wrong proof to check if verify is working correctly


# TestSolnSquareVerifier

Write test contract for ZK and ERC721 integration:

- initialize SquareVerifier contract and use address into constructor of SolnSquareVerifier. It will be used to verify trx when you mint using proof
  
- 1 - Test if a new solution can be added for contract : try to use method addSolution who will a solution into relative mapping 

- 2 - token can be minted : try to mint a new token with method mintNewNFT which will mint new token with relative owner, tokenId and It will use input proof to verify transaction

- 3 - check tokenName and symbol : check if name and symbol are filled correctly
